<center><div class="jumbotron">
  <h1><font color="#00BFFF"><b>HOW TO CHANGE TRANSMISSION FLUID</b></font></h1>
</div>

<!--Write in the steps-->

<ul class="list-group">
  <li class="list-group-item">1.) Lift the car with a jack or car ramps.</a></li>
  <li class="list-group-item">2.) Locate the transmission fluid pan.  It should be directly under the transmission with 6 to 8 bolts holding it in place.</a></li>
  <li class="list-group-item">3.) Drain the fluid.  If the oil pan has a drain plug, remove the plug to drain the fluid into a pan.  If there is no drain plug, you will have to remove the entire pan.  Using the latter method is the only way to change the transmission filter if need be.  </a></li>
  <li class="list-group-item">4.) After draining, replace drain plug or entire pan and lower the vehicle.</a></li>
  <li class="list-group-item">5.) Locate the transmission fluid dipstick.  It usually has an image of a lock, and is NOT labeled “Oil” or “Engine Oil”.</a></li>
  <li class="list-group-item">6.) Add new Motorcraft fluid in the spout.</a></li>
</ul>

